Title: _app.admin.print-jobs._index page
Route file: web/routes/_app.admin.print-jobs._index.tsx
Suggested path: /app/admin/print-jobs

Role/Purpose
- Provide system-wide view of print jobs across all vendors with KPIs (active queue, awaiting schedule, next scheduled run).
- Enable creating new print jobs and navigating to job details for monitoring and management.

Primary UI Components
- `PageHeader` with title "Print jobs", dynamic description showing total count, and "New job" button action.
- Optional `Alert` banner when `isSample === true` showing "Sample dataset" message with error details.
- Three KPI `Card`s displaying: Active queue (with status breakdown), Awaiting schedule count, Next scheduled run date/time.
- `Card`-wrapped custom `Table` component from `@/components/ui/table` with columns: Job, Status, Print date, Order.
- Table rows use `StatusBadge` component for status display and are keyboard accessible.

Data Dependencies
- Loader calls `context.api.printJob.findMany()` with select: `id`, `printJobId`, `status`, `printDate`, `order.orderId`.
- Sorted by `printDate: "Descending"`, limited to `first: 250`.
- Computes stats via `computeStats()` helper: `total`, `statusCounts` (record of status -> count), `awaitingSchedule` (jobs without printDate), `nextScheduledAt` (earliest upcoming date).
- On error, returns `sampleJobs` array (4 curated records) with `isSample: true` and `errorMessage`.
- Jobs mapped to `LoaderJob` type with normalized status values.

Actions & Side Effects
- "New job" button navigates to `/admin/print-jobs/new`.
- Table row click/keyboard activation navigates to `/admin/print-jobs/:id`.
- Alert displays when showing sample data with error message surfaced.
- Status badges use `StatusBadge` component with `kind="printJob"` for consistent styling.

Acceptance Criteria
- Loader handles API success and failure gracefully with sample data fallback.
- KPI cards reflect current data: total jobs, status breakdown, awaiting schedule count, next scheduled date.
- Sample data fallback shows alert with error message when API unavailable.
- Table renders job ID, status badge, formatted print date, and order ID.
- Status badges display correctly with appropriate colors/variants.
- Row click/keyboard navigation works correctly to detail page.
- New job button navigates to create page.
- Empty state shows "No print jobs found." when array is empty.
- Date formatting uses `Intl.DateTimeFormat` with medium date and short time styles.

QA & Tests
- Manual: Simulate API failure to verify sample data + alert appears.
- Manual: Verify KPI calculations match table data (status counts, awaiting schedule).
- Manual: Test keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter, Space) on table rows.
- Manual: Verify row click navigates to detail page.
- Manual: Check date formatting displays correctly for various timezones.
- Unit: Test `computeStats` helper with various job arrays and edge cases.
- E2E: Test full flow from list → row click → detail navigation.

Notes
- Loader implements robust error handling with sample data fallback pattern.
- Custom Table component used instead of AutoTable for better control and accessibility.
- Status order array used for consistent KPI display: ["pending", "printing", "complete", "failed"].
- Print date formatting handles null values gracefully (shows "—").
- Consider pagination when job volume exceeds 250 records.
